cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling and speech recognition. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it involves acoustic modeling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves building models that can learn and adapt to new languages. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves building models that can transfer knowledge across languages. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves building models that can bring different languages together in a universal space.
